here with our pigs in the forest, so our farming&nbsp;
philosophy really is based around our animals&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:12.560 --> 00:00:16.480
when we started farming it was coming&nbsp;
from a background in animal welfare&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:16.480 --> 00:00:25.120
so our main goal is to raise our animals in an as&nbsp;
humane a way as possible while also respecting our&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:25.120 --> 00:00:32.880
farm so we want to be as sustainable and holistic&nbsp;
as we can, we've been raising pigs since 2015&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:33.440 --> 00:00:39.840
but we also have a large focus on grass-fed&nbsp;
sheep and we've started raising grass-fed&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:39.840 --> 00:00:44.560
beef as well in the last couple years and just&nbsp;
to round it out we have a flock of laying hens

00:00:45.440 --> 00:00:51.360
so our sows are all purebred berkshires, they're&nbsp;
known as the kobe beef of pork and we're really&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:51.360 --> 00:00:57.440
not interested in any lean meats here so we really&nbsp;
want that marbling and then we crossbreed them&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:57.440 --> 00:01:03.840
with a duroc boar which is a more modern breed&nbsp;
but it has the most marbling of all the commercial&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:03.840 --> 00:01:10.720
pigs, well the pigs here they're omnivores like we&nbsp;
are so they need complete protein in their diet&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:10.720 --> 00:01:15.520
but they're also really great foragers so&nbsp;
they do eat a lot of grass in our pasture&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:15.520 --> 00:01:21.840
as well as nuts and roots and bugs that they&nbsp;
find on the ground but we of course have to&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:21.840 --> 00:01:27.520
feed them as well they need complete protein and&nbsp;
the best source of protein for pigs is from grain&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:27.520 --> 00:01:36.800
so we feed a balanced diet of field peas&nbsp;
barley and oats, the the ratio sort of varies&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:36.800 --> 00:01:42.880
throughout the year but no soy no corn for our&nbsp;
pigs and of course we we add you know minerals&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:42.880 --> 00:01:49.360
and vitamins that they need to their diet and&nbsp;
then it sort of varies with the season so in the&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:49.360 --> 00:01:53.840
fall of course they're getting seasonal&nbsp;
fruit and vegetables so lots of apples and pears&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:54.800 --> 00:02:01.200
donated from our customers and then in later&nbsp;
in the season they'll get lots of pumpkins but&nbsp;&nbsp;

